DescriptiveText.text: Andaz Scottsdale is a desert oasis featuring stunning views of Camelback Mountain. Mid-century, desert inspired interiors conceived by EDG Interior Architecture plus Design draw inspiration from the innovative 1950s desert art scene influenced by architects, artists and graphic designers including Alexander Girard, Frank Lloyd Wright and Paolo Solari.  Andaz Scottsdale includes 185 guestrooms and suites, ranging in size from 350 to 500 square feet configured in bungalow style clusters of six units each to provide guests an authentic and intimate desert resort experience. Guestrooms feature state-of-the-art technology and entertainment, as well as private terraces, including some with outdoor showers. The resort includes a large pool and sundeck with a luxurious 12000 square foot spa facility and a fitness center featuring the latest cardio and strength exercise equipment. Inspired by the spirit of artistic expression which radiates through the hotel, food and beverage offerings at Andaz Scottsdale encourage and promote culinary experimentation. A glass box display kitchen features a plancha grill where the chef will create innovative twists on local flavors from a palette of the finest fresh ingredients.  The menu encourages social interaction – from a Southwest infused breakfast to shareable plate options throughout the day and evening. The lounge is centered around an open mixology hub and provides an eclectic mix of signature cocktails, craft beers and tap beverages. Guests imagination will be inspired by the stunning colors of the desert sky against the silhouette of Camelback Mountain  from the outdoor terrace.

DescriptiveText.text: Soaring above the bustling and hustling streets in the fabulous Suning Plaza skyscraper, Hyatt Regency Wuxi offers a privileged location in the heart of Wuxi city, occupying floors 43 to 67 of the North tower of the Suning Plaza, makes it the highest hotel in Wuxi. Hotel is within walking distance of the city’s main business, shopping and entertainment centers in Chong An District as well as located at the intersection of the 1 and 2 subway lines, with easy access to Wuxi Railway Station, Wuxi East Railway Station and major city landmarks. The hotel is 30 minutes away from Wuxi Sunan International Airport, 25 minutes from the Turtle Head Park and 10 minutes from Xihui Park.Hyatt Regency Wuxi offers 345 well-appointed guestrooms including 36 luxury suites, ranging in size from 42 sq m up to 280 sq m, each outfitted with stylish contemporary furnishings. Located on floors 45 through 63, guests can take in sweeping views of the city skyline from any of its rooms and suites.Four restaurants and lounges, ranging from casual to fine dining awaits for you to explore. Enjoy authentic local Wuxi and Huaiyang cuisine together with roasted Peiking Duck at Chinese restaurant, a mix-and-match combination of Chinese noodles and dim sum at Mian Dian, simply unwind at the international buffet restaurant Market Cafe, enjoy simple yet sophisticated light dishes and a cup of your favorite coffee or tea at the Lounge and Soak in breath-taking 360-degree panoramic views , or sophisticated Mediterranean flavours of grilled and seafood delicacies at Italian restaurant- La Cucina at the very top of Hotel.Hyatt Regency Wuxi features extensive meeting space and event facilities covering up to 1,880 sq m, including an 800 sq m pillar-less Grand Ballroom and eight multi-functional event venues, perfect for weddings, parties and conferences. Two unique Sky Rooms on top of the hotel (67th floor) offer the best place to host high-end parties and stylish entertainment.Hyatt Regency Wuxi’s leisure centre provides much-needed rejuvenation. Enjoy an invigorating workout at our fully equipped fitness center, take a dip in its 25m indoor heated swimming pool or pamper yourself with a relaxing treatment at the spa. Whether you are here for business or leisure, we look forward to welcoming you to Hyatt Regency Wuxi.
